The new code is actually correct. It works because of the line above. epochMillis is computed by taking into account nanoOfSecond / NANOSECONDS_PER_MILLISECOND. The remainder is stored in picosOfMilli.
It would actually be clearer to do it the other way around. I'll update it.
long epochMillis = base.toEpochSecond() * MILLISECONDS_PER_SECOND + nanoOfSecond / NANOSECONDS_PER_MILLISECOND;
int picosOfMilli = (nanoOfSecond % NANOSECONDS_PER_MILLISECOND) * PICOSECONDS_PER_NANOSECOND;

